read_rbind <- function(list, list2 = NULL) {
    out <- data.frame()
    for (i in 1:length(list)) {
        print(paste0("reading in ", list[i]))
        
        x <- read.csv(list[i], stringsAsFactors = F)
        if (is.null(list2) == F) {
            x$run = list2[i]
            print(paste0("appending run column: ", list2[i]))
        }
        out <- rbind(x, out)
    }
    return(out)
}

# The problem here is that it does not include the cases where no variants
# are found.  These add_missing functions correct that. This is a helper
# function to add the cases where there were no variants called.
add_missing.intervention <- function(x) {
    missing_chr <- levels(x$chr)[!((levels(x$chr) %in% as.character(x$chr)))]
    if (length(missing_chr) > 0) {
        for (i in 1:length(missing_chr)) {
            x <- rbind(x, data.frame(Intervention = unique(x$Intervention), 
                chr = missing_chr[i], Id = unique(x$Id), iSNV = 0, n = unique(x$n)))
        }
    }
    return(x)
}

add_missing.HAI <- function(x) {
    # This is a helper function to add the cases where there were no variants
    # called.
    missing_chr <- levels(x$chr)[!((levels(x$chr) %in% as.character(x$chr)))]
    if (length(missing_chr) > 0) {
        for (i in 1:length(missing_chr)) {
            x <- rbind(x, data.frame(HAI.cut = unique(x$HAI.cut), chr = missing_chr[i], 
                Id = unique(x$Id), iSNV = 0, n = unique(x$n)))
        }
    }
    return(x)
}

count_tables <- function(data, return = F) {
    intervention.chr.counts <- ddply(data, ~Intervention + chr + Id, summarize, 
        iSNV = length(mutation))
    
    intervention.chr.counts$chr <- factor(intervention.chr.counts$chr, levels = c("PB2", 
        "PB1", "PA", "HA", "NP", "NR", "M", "NS"))
    
    
    columns <- unique(intervention.chr.counts$Intervention)
    intervention.chr.counts$n = 0
    for (i in 1:length(columns)) {
        # How many samples are there in each intervention
        x <- length(unique(intervention.chr.counts$Id[which(intervention.chr.counts$Intervention == 
            columns[i])]))
        intervention.chr.counts$n[which(intervention.chr.counts$Intervention == 
            columns[i])] = x
    }
    
    intervention.chr.counts <- mutate(intervention.chr.counts, Intervention = paste0(Intervention, 
        " ", "(n=", n, ")"))
    
    # I need to add the cases where no variants were found.
    
    intervention.chr.counts <- ddply(intervention.chr.counts, ~Id, add_missing.intervention)
    
    intervention.chr.sum <- ddply(intervention.chr.counts, ~Intervention + chr, 
        summarize, mean_iSNV = mean(iSNV), range = IQR(iSNV))
    
    intervention.chr.tab <- mutate(intervention.chr.sum, iSNV = paste0(round(mean_iSNV, 
        2), "  ", "(", range, ")"))
    intervention.chr.table <- dcast(intervention.chr.tab, chr ~ Intervention, 
        value.var = "iSNV")
    # knitr::kable(qual.chr.table)
    
    HAI.chr.counts <- ddply(data, ~HAI.cut + chr + Id, summarize, iSNV = length(mutation))
    HAI.chr.counts$chr <- factor(HAI.chr.counts$chr, levels = c("PB2", "PB1", 
        "PA", "HA", "NP", "NR", "M", "NS"))
    
    HAI.chr.counts <- mutate(HAI.chr.counts, HAI.cut = ifelse(HAI.cut, yes = " 40", 
        no = "< 40"))
    
    columns <- unique(HAI.chr.counts$HAI.cut)
    HAI.chr.counts$n = 0
    for (i in 1:length(columns)) {
        x <- length(unique(HAI.chr.counts$Id[which(HAI.chr.counts$HAI.cut == 
            columns[i])]))
        HAI.chr.counts$n[which(HAI.chr.counts$HAI.cut == columns[i])] = x
    }
    
    HAI.chr.counts <- mutate(HAI.chr.counts, HAI.cut = paste0(HAI.cut, " ", 
        "(n=", n, ")"))
    
    HAI.chr.counts <- ddply(HAI.chr.counts, ~Id, add_missing.HAI)
    
    HAI.chr.sum <- ddply(HAI.chr.counts, ~HAI.cut + chr, summarize, mean_iSNV = mean(iSNV), 
        range = IQR(iSNV))
    
    HAI.chr.tab <- mutate(HAI.chr.sum, iSNV = paste0(round(mean_iSNV, 2), "  ", 
        "(", range, ")"))
    HAI.chr.table <- dcast(HAI.chr.tab, chr ~ HAI.cut, value.var = "iSNV")
    # knitr::kable(HAI.chr.table)
    all <- join_all(dfs = list(HAI.chr.table, intervention.chr.table), by = "chr")
    
    all$chr <- factor(all$chr, levels = c("PB2", "PB1", "PA", "HA", "NP", "NR", 
        "M", "NS"))
    
    all <- all[order(all$chr, decreasing = F), ]
    
    if (return == T) {
        return(list(HAI.chr.counts, intervention.chr.counts))
    }
    knitr::kable(all)
    
    
}

check_titers <- function(data) {
    H <- mutate(data, H = HAI.geo + HAI.cut)
    print("HAI not equal")
    print(unique(H$Id[H$H == 1]))
    
    N <- subset(data, N = NAI.geo + NAI.cut)
    print("NAI not equal")
    print(unique(N$Id[N$N == 1]))
    
}

check_titers(minor.04.05)
check_titers(minor.05.06)
check_titers(minor.07.08)
